{
  "doc_id": "19953",
  "text": "Ultrasonography performed by an expert examiner might be a useful strategy for staging and treatment planning [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Recently, it was shown that a detailed transabdominal and transvaginal ultrasound examination, performed by an expert examiner, could render a similar diagnostic performance to CT for assessing pelvic/abdominal tumor spread disease in women with EOC [CITATION_4] . Lung ultrasonography is a recognized imaging modality that can be successfully used in many conditions including cancer [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . In a general population of patients with pleural effusions, one could suspect malignant effusions based on ultrasonographic findings [CITATION_7] . Thus, comprehensive ultrasound staging with lung ultrasonography could be considered as an alternative imaging modality to CT scanning of patients with EOC in specific settings.",
